alajara, Buenos Aires y Rio de Janeiro y la promoción de las literaturas extranjeras a través del formato del "invitado de honor" -- tMediación editorial y dinámicas actuales de la circulación internacional -- t(World) Literature in the Digital Age -- tNuevos escenarios literarios -- tReading in the Digital Age -- tBetween Digital Transformation in Libraries and the Digital Humanities -- tAutomation Approaches to Book Licensing -- tEl imparable crecimiento de los microformatos literarios digitales -- tEditing World Literature - Two Roundtables -- tRoundtable World Editors -- tRoundtable Global Book Markets0 aOpen Accessuhttps://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_abf2funrestricted online access2star  aThe existence of World Literature depends on specific processes, institutions, and actors involved in the global circulation of literary works. The contributions of this volume aim to pay attention to these multiple material dimensions of Latin American 20th and 21st century literatures. From perspectives informed by materialism, sociology, book studies, and digital humanities, the articles of this volume analyze the role of publishing houses, politics of translation, mediators and gatekeepers, allowing insights into the processes that enable books to cross borders and to be transformed into globally circulating commodities. The book focusses both on material (re)sources of literary archives, key actors in literary and cultural markets, prizes and book fairs, as well as on recent dimension of the digital age. Statements of some of the leading representatives of the global publishing world complement these analyses of the operations of selection and aggregation of value to literary texts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on o